# Generated by Cargo
# will have compiled files and executables
debug/
target/

# These are backup files generated by rustfmt
**/*.rs.bk

# MSVC Windows builds of rustc generate these, which store debugging information
*.pdb

# Linux core dumps (produced when a release binary crashes — 2-3 MB
# each and must not be synced through the filestore).
core.*

# Converted Kokoro model weights and voices (~341MB).
# These are reproduced on demand by `python3 weight_converter.py
# --huggingface hexgrad/Kokoro-82M --output ferrocarril_weights`
# and must not be checked in or synced through the filestore — they will
# overwhelm mutagen and reset the sandbox.
ferrocarril_weights/
real_kokoro_weights/
**/ferrocarril_weights/
**/real_kokoro_weights/

# Demo / test audio outputs
*.wav
demo_audio.wav
test_output/

# wasm-bindgen output for the ferrocarril-wasm demo. Rebuilt on
# demand via `ferrocarril-wasm/demo/build.sh`. The Pages workflow
# regenerates this fresh in CI, and local developers rebuild it
# after any Rust change, so it should never be checked in.
ferrocarril-wasm/demo/pkg/

# RustRover
#  JetBrains specific template is maintained in a separate JetBrains.gitignore that can
#  be found at https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/Global/JetBrains.gitignore
#  and can be added to the global gitignore or merged into this file.  For a more nuclear
#  option (not recommended) you can uncomment the following to ignore the entire idea folder.
#.idea/